you were quite the journey. an adventure, really. from san diego to dallas, and now in my forever home in Charlotte. Everything i learned in year 27 was meant for so much more than i ever could’ve imagined. I explored depths of myself I never thought i’d be brave enough to look at, gained and lost a few good souls, and found the absolute love of my life. 27 was f a r from easy, but everything about it proved to be worth it. 
.

here’s to year 28– i pray for more growth, laughs, and a whole lotta love. remember to always honor your truth & keep the right people around you. 🖤

one year from now, will you look back and realize you let the lies and doubts keep you from tapping into your full potential and owning that confidence you know is inside of you? or will you instead look back and be so proud of the steps you took FOR YOURSELF, the bets you placed ON YOU and your ABILITY to make a change and love every step of the process!? Don’t let another week, month, year go by hiding in the fear of change. YOU are able. YOU deserve to prioritize yourself and be CONFIDENT again. Whatever that looks like for you. Choose the steps forward, don’t stand still. 🫶🏽✨

Stop caring about what other people have to say about you, if you want to have a better life and mindset. It's what you tell yourself that matters.
Other people's opinions do NOT matter as long as you know you're doing the right thing. Never feel ashamed to take the steps you think are right. Decide for YOURSELF what is good and stick 👏🏽to 👏🏽it. 

Stop measuring your self-worth by the mediocre standards others have.✨

reminder to you, reminder to self—

you are the only one in control of what you CHOOSE to do. 

no matter what thoughts you’re holding or what feelings you’re experiencing, you still have the power of choice. 

whenever you make a commitment to yourself, or others for that matter, it is on you to honor that commitment and show up for what is expected and required to see it all through to success. 

fitness journeys, relationships, friendships, work, etc. they all take commitment. they all have ups and downs. 

how you feel about it one day won’t necessarily be how you feel about it every day. 

and that’s o k a y. 

but what’s not okay is to let those feelings and thoughts, dictate and control your choices. 

i challenge all of you to make an effort to prioritize your choices over validating your feelings. 

be mindful. extend grace. and do it anyway. 

it makes a difference. xo.
are you doing the things that make you happy?

how many times have you talked yourself out of just getting shit done? 

“i’ll do it later.”

“diet starts monday”

“i’m not ready, i’ll start the next round”

“what if i fail”

imma keep it real honest with ya— there’s N E V E R a perfect time to start anything that forces you to get out of your comfort zone and make some real deal changes. 

there will always be something that comes up. something already planned. birthdays. vacations. unexpected mishaps. 

so at what point do you just say “screw it. i deserve to honor me and make some shit shake” 

you already know what it takes. it’s time to start believing you have every ounce of what it takes, in you. 

make the step. thank me later.
